                     <finalRubric>Explicit Liber meditacionum Saluatoris nostri Ihesu Christi et
                        beatissime matris eius Marie</finalRubric>
                     <incipit>O
                        Domine sancte Pater omnipotens, propter potenciam</incipit>
                     <note>A devotional commentary on the Life of our
                        Lord and of the Virgin Mary, in five parts, each containing five quindenae
                        and each quindena fifteen meditations, of which a full table or 'Kalendar'
                        precedes the text: see fols. 1, 21v, 47v, 76v, 114. A substituted piece is
                        posted on fol. 45.</note>
                     <note>The text is also found in BL Royal MS. 8 C. xv; for a brief summary see A. I. Doyle and Ralph Hanna, <title>Hope Allenâ€™s Writings Ascribed to Richard Rolle: A Corrected List of Copies</title>, Publications of the Journal of Medieval Latin (2019), pp. 57-8. It is a compilation from various authorities including <persName role="aut" key="person_51685861">Bridget of Sweden</persName>; the borrowings from <persName role="aut" key="person_2465074">Richard Rolle</persName> are listed ibid., pp. 57-8. </note>
